text: Harry Robert Charles Came (born 27 August 1998) is an English cricketer. He made his first-class debut on 20 August 2019, for Hampshire in the 2019 County Championship, as a concussion replacement for Aneurin Donald. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:English cricketers Category:Hampshire cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:English cricketers of the 21st century
